{"title_page": "Dave Tofani", "text_new": "'''Dave Tofani''' is an American [[saxophonist]] and [[woodwind]] player, and composer. As a session musician he has performed on over 500 jazz, pop, and rock recordings such as the clarinet solo on [[Say Hello, Wave Goodbye|\"Say Hello, Wave Goodbye\"]] by [[Soft Cell]].<ref name=\"allmusic\">AllMusic [{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=mn0000678578/biography|pure_url=yes}} Dave Tofani : Biography].</ref>\n\n== Collaborations ==\n* ''[[Closeup (Frankie Valli album)|Closeup]]'' - [[Frankie Valli]] (1975)\n* ''[[Good King Bad]]'' - [[George Benson]] (1976)\n* ''[[Never Letting Go]]'' - [[Phoebe Snow]] (1977)\n* ''[[Thighs and Whispers]]'' - [[Bette Midler]] (1979)\n* ''[[Naughty (album)|Naughty]]'' - [[Chaka Khan]] (1980)\n* ''[[Double Fantasy]]'' - [[John Lennon]], [[Yoko Ono]] (1980)\n* ''[[Aretha (1980 album)|Aretha]]'' - [[Aretha Franklin]] (1980)\n* ''[[Chaka Khan (album)|Chaka Khan]]'' - [[Chaka Khan]] (1982)\n* ''I'll Keep On Loving You'' - [[Linda Clifford]] (1982)\n* ''[[The Nightfly]]'' - [[Donald Fagen]] (1982)\n* ''[[Gloria Gaynor (album)|Gloria Gaynor]]'' - [[Gloria Gaynor]] (1982)\n* ''[[Pacific Fire]]'' - [[George Benson]] (1983)\n* ''[[Passionfruit (album)|Passionfuit]]'' - [[Michael Franks (musician)|Michael Franks]] (1983)\n* ''[[Civilized Man]]'' - [[Joe Cocker]] (1984)\n* ''[[No Sound But a Heart]]'' - [[Sheena Easton]] (1987)\n* ''[[Bulletproof Heart]]'' - [[Grace Jones]] (1989)\n* ''[[Am I Not Your Girl?]]'' - [[Sin\u00e9ad O'Connor]] (1992)\n* ''[[Kamakiriad]]'' - [[Donald Fagen]] (1993)\n* ''[[Snowfall on the Sahara]]'' - [[Natalie Cole]] (1999)\n* ''[[Songs from the Last Century]]'' - [[George Michael]] (1999)\n* ''Nature Boy: The Standards Album'' - [[Aaron Neville]] (2003)\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tofani, David}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American saxophonists]]\n[[Category:American male saxophonists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American composers]]